                "verse",
                "v1",
                "note",
                "f"
              ],
              "value": "tn Or “and look, Esau was coming.” By the use of the particle הִנֵּה (hinneh, “look”), the narrator invites the reader to view the scene through Jacob’s eyes."
            },
            {
              "rowId": 8,
              "keyParts": [
                8,
                "p1",
                "verse",
                "v1",
                "content"
              ],
              "value": "along with four hundred men. So he divided the children among Leah, Rachel, and the two female servants."
            },
            {
