              "keyParts": [
                "v001_NET_GEN_033",
                9,
                "p1",
                "verse",
                "v1",
                "plain_text"
              ],
              "value": "1 Jacob looked up and saw that Esau was coming along with four hundred men. So he divided the children among Leah, Rachel, and the two female servants."
            },
            {
              "rowId": 10,
              "keyParts": [
                10,
                "p1",
                "verse",
                "v2",
                "label"
              ],
              "value": "2"
            },
            {
              "rowId": 11,
              "keyParts": [
                11,
                "p1",
                "verse",
                "v2",
                "content"
              ],
              "value": "He put the servants and their children in front, with Leah and her children behind them, and Rachel and Joseph behind them."
            },
            {
              "rowId": 12,
              "keyParts": [
                12,
                "p1",
                "verse",
                "v2",
                "note",
                "f"
              ],
              "value": "sn This kind of ranking according to favoritism no doubt fed the jealousy over Joseph that later becomes an important element in the narrative. It must have been painful to the family to see that they were expendable."
            },
            {
              "rowId": 13,
              "keyParts": [
                "v002_NET_GEN_033",
                13,
                "p1",
                "verse",
                "v2",
                "plain_text"
              ],
              "value": "2 He put the servants and their children in front, with Leah and her children behind them, and Rachel and Joseph behind them."
